In epidemiology of communicable (infectious) diseases, the serial interval of a pathogen is the time period between infection by an organism to the transmission (infectious) period.

Serial intervals can vary widely. The serial interval for SARs was 7 days [http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/300/5627/1966 Transmission Dynamics and Control of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome]